Business Brief -- Kerr Glass Manufacturing Corp.:
   Widened Losses Are Posted
   For Fourth Quarter, Year
For the full year, Kerr's loss widened to $2.6 million, or
93 cents a share, from $1.3 million, or 57 cents a share.
Sales fell 3.4% to $145.4 million from $150.4 million.
   Kerr said the sale of its glass container business to Ball
Corp of Muncie, Ind., will enable it to focus on its plastic
packaging, home-canning supplies and other businesses. The
companies announced the completion of the sale yesterday.